    <subfield code="a">Resident of Oakfield Township, Kent County, Mich., who served in Co. C, 13th Michigan Infantry, during the Civil War.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Chiefly letters to Tower from his father Samuel Tower and other relatives, describing life in Kent County during the war; also letters written by other members of the 13th Michigan Infantry to Tower after he was wounded in 1863 and separated from his unit; describing their activities in Georgia; and letters from Tower's cousin Eustace Tower, a soldier in the 13th Battery of Michigan Artillery, describing garrison duty near Washington, D.C., and the search for the assassins of Abraham Lincoln.</subfield>
